{"annotator": "Maggie Wang", "original_name": "anthropic", "revised_name": "seed1_ep1_optimal", "score": -0.52, "label": "leaning no", "feedback": "- \"rejecting biases\" is very broad, and makes Rule 4 more ambiguous in my opinion. What is \"procedural fairness\"?\n- Rule 5 is technically more explicit, and even helpful, but it feels somewhat arbitrary to call out this one specific addition of \"controversial ideas\" relative to others.\n- I agree with the addition of Rule 21\n- Rule 46: what are \"established ethical norms\"\n- Rule 54 is inherently ambiguous, not even sure what intent they had in the first place", "timestamp": 1775768002.246627}
